Mr. Garrett,



                Your e-mail to the Governor was forwarded to my office at the Department of Labor, Wage and Hour Division.   The issues you are pursuing deal with your termination and unemployment.  The Wage and Hour Act does not deal with the hiring or firing of Employees but rather the collection of earned wages.  North Carolina is a right to work state and that means that an Employee can be terminated at any time for any reason.   In fact, the Employer does not have to give you a reason.  If you file for unemployment, the Employer would have to state a reason or allow you to draw unemployment against his account if you are eligible.  So, as far as your termination is concerned, we cannot help.  Your unemployment would be a matter to be handled by your local Employment Security Commission.  If you are not getting a reasonable response from the person you are dealing with there, you may need to contact their boss or that location’s manager.  I hope that this will clarify the issue.


