How Employers treat their Employees is up to the company except for discrimination.  The discrimination that is illegal is based on age, race, sex, religion, national origin, handicap or color.   The fact that the Employer does not like you (and therefore treats you worse that other Employees) is not illegal.  If the Employer wants to treat the office staff one way and the production staff differently, that is not illegal.  However, if the office staff is all female and the production staff is all male, then there might be a sex discrimination issue.  Or, if the Employees of department A are all minorities and the Employees of department B are all white there could be a race issue.  But if the Employer just likes one group of Employees better than another group and therefore treats them better, this is not illegal.  It may be unfair, but it is not illegal.  It is the Employer’s business and he/she can run it the way they want to.  How the Employer treats the Employees is up to the company as long as the Employer does not violate the rights of Employees based on the protected areas.  It is not illegal to be a poor manager and it is not illegal to find another job if you have a poor manager.  Employee treatment is an issue that is also dealt with by labor unions. 




