Under the North Carolina Wage and Hour Act, there are no laws requiring breaks for any Employees age 16 and older.  Therefore, anyone 16 years old and older could be worked 24 hours per day, 7 days per week provided the Employer pays the proper wage (Minimum Wage or more) and Overtime.   Most Employers have found that they get more work and better work from Employees that get breaks, but the breaks are not required by law.  Also, there are no maximum hour laws for Employees over 16.  Years ago, Employees could only work 56 hours per week, but due to complaints by Employees who wanted to work more than 56 hours per week, that law was repealed back in the 70’s or early 80’s.  If you have any questions, please call me.




